Recursion is a rather advanced topic that may best be explored somewhere down the road when all the basic concepts are cemented in your thinking. That being said, letâ€™s consider a recursion for Factorialâ€¦
function factorial(n) {
    if (n < 0) {
        return 0;
    }
    if (n === 0 || n === 1) {        // base case
        return 1;
    } else {
        return n * factorial(n - 1)  // recursive case
    }
}

console.log(factorial(7))            // <- 5040

There are other topics on recursion in the forums which may help illustrate and explain the above, and the concept in general. The thing to note is that every case returns something, namely another call (except for the base case).

